        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Fan Yong",
          "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
          "date": "2016-06-05 11:55:20.000000000",
          "tz": 480
        },
        "subject": "LU-6756 osd-zfs: not hold rwlock to do blocked operation",
        "message": "LU-6756 osd-zfs: not hold rwlock to do blocked operation\n\nFor osd_object_sa_dirty_rele(), the caller may holds the rwlock\nobj::oo_attr_lock to do get another rw_semaphore and do blocked\nxattr update. If it is blocked, then will tigger soft lockup.\n\nSo the caller should release obj::oo_attr_lock just after unlink\nfrom the transaction delay EA update list osd_thandle::ot_sa_list.\n\nSigned-off-by: Fan Yong <fan.yong@intel.com>\nChange-Id: I52454e1275e15ea24974dd737535b71af37b0095\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
